forms anastomoses with its contralateral partner.\twikipedia:Inferior_alveolar_artery\t\t\tUBERON:0014693\tUBERON:0009679\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600094\tintra-acinar arteriole\t\tUBERON:0001980\tUBERON:0008874\tAn arteriole that branches from the pulmonary arteriole and supplies deoxygenated blood to the pulmonary capillaries in the alveoli of the lungs.\tPMID:20110543\t\t\tUBERON:8600077\tUBERON:0002299\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600095\tascending palatine artery\tFMA:49555\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0001456\t\"An artery that branches from the facial artery, and branches to supply the soft palate and the palatine tonsil.\"\twikipedia:Ascending_palatine_artery\t\t\tUBERON:0001612\tUBERON:0002373|UBERON:0001733\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600096\tsubmental artery\tFMA:49561\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0001456\t\"An artery that branches from the facial artery that runs forward under the mouth, then turns upward upon reaching the chin.\"\twikipedia:Submental_artery\t\t\tUBERON:0001612\t\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600097\tdeep lingual artery\tFMA:49532\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0001456\t\"An artery that branches from the lingual artery and supplies blood to the tongue itself, particularly the body and tip of the tongue. The deep lingual artery travels superiorly in a tortuous course along the under (ventral) surface of the tongue, below the longitudinalis inferior, and above the mucous membrane.\"\twikipedia:Lingual_artery\tthird part of lingual artery\tFMA:49532\tUBERON:0001610\tUBERON:0001723\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600098\tdorsal lingual artery\tFMA:49546\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0001456\t\"An artery that branches from the lingual artery and supplies the soft palate, tonsils, epiglottis, palatoglossal arch, and adjacent mucous membrane. The dorsal lingual artery runs along the upper border of the hyoid bone and anastomises with its fellow of the opposite side.\"\thttps://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK554513/\t\t\tUBERON:0001610\tUBERON:0002373|UBERON:0001733|UBERON:0000388|UBERON:0011640\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600099\taccessory meningeal artery\tFMA:79467\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000033\t\"An artery that branches from the maxillary artery and supplies the meninges. The accessory meningeal artery ascends through the foramen ovale to enter the cranial cavity and supply the dura mater of the floor of the middle cranial fossa and of the trigeminal cave, and to the trigeminal ganglion.\"\twikipedia:Accessory_meningeal_artery\t\t\tUBERON:0001616\tUBERON:0010743\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600100\tartery of pterygoid canal\tFMA:85528\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0001456\t\"An artery that branches from the maxillary artery and supplies blood to structures in the auditory tube, tympanic cavity, and upper pharynx. The artery of the pterygoid canal courses through the pterygoid canal, a small bony canal located in the sphenoid bone of the skull.\"\twikipedia:Artery_of_the_pterygoid_canal\t\t\tUBERON:0001616\tUBERON:0006562|UBERON:0001756|UBERON:0002393\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600101\tdescending palatine artery\tFMA:49791\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0001456\tAn artery that branches from the maxillary artery and supplies the hard and soft palate.\twikipedia:Descending_palatine_artery\t\t\tUBERON:0001616\tUBERON:0003216|UBERON:0001733\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600102\tleft anterior descending artery\tFMA:3862\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000915\t\"An artery that branches from the left coronary artery and supplies the anterior wall of the left ventricle, the interventricular septum, and the apex of the heart.\"\twikipedia:Left_anterior_descending_artery\tanterior interventricular branch of left coronary artery\tFMA:3862\tUBERON:0001626\t\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600106\tanterior humeral circumflex artery\tFMA:22680\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0001467\t\"An artery that branches from the axilliary artery and supplies the deltoid, biceps brachii, and coracobrachialis muscles, the glenohumeral joint, the proximal humeral head, and the skin overlying the anterior aspect of the proximal humerus. This artery courses laterally across the anterior surface of the humerus and anastomoses with the posterior humeral circumflex artery.\"\thttps://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/anterior-circumflex-humeral-artery/20091\t\t\tUBERON:0001394\tUBERON:0001476|UBERON:0001507|UBERON:0001505|UBERON:0001470|UBERON:0006801|UBERON:0004263\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-08-20T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600107\tposterior humeral circumflex artery\tFMA:22684\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0001467\t\"An artery that branches from the axilliary artery and supplies the deltoid, teres major, teres minor, and long and lateral heads of the triceps brachii muscles, glenohumeral joint, and the cutaneous supply to the area posterolateral to the proximal humerus. This artery courses posteriorly with the axillary nerve, through the quadrangular space, to the posterior aspect of the humerus and anastomoses with the anterior humeral circumflex artery.\"\thttps://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/posterior-circumflex-humeral-artery/24676\t\t\tUBERON:0001394\tUBERON:0001476|UBERON:0001478|UBERON:0010496|UBERON:0001509|UBERON:0001470|UBERON:0004263\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-08-20T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8920000\tanterior ciliary artery\tFMA:49962\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000970\tAn artery that branches from the ophthalmic artery and supplies the anterior segment of the eyeball and ciliary body.\twikipedia:Anterior_ciliary_arteries|PMID:30725748\t\t\tUBERON:0001619\tUBERON:0001811|UBERON:0001773|UBERON:0006533|UBERON:0001775\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t25/03/2025 16:52:04\r\nUBERON:8920001\tshort posterior ciliary artery\tFMA:70777\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000970\tAn artery that branches from the ophthalmic artery and supplies the choroid and ciliary processes.\twikipedia:Short_posterior_ciliary_arteries|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/short-posterior-ciliary-arteries-left/16689\tSet of short posterior ciliary arteries|Short posterior ciliary arteries\tFMA:70777\tUBERON:0001619\tUBERON:0001776|UBERON:0010427\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t25/03/2025 16:52:04\r\nUBERON:8920002\tlong posterior ciliary artery\tFMA:70778\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000970\tAn artery that branches from the ophthalmic artery and supplies the choroid, ciliary body and iris. \twikipedia:Long_posterior_ciliary_arteries|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/long-posterior-ciliary-arteries-right/23957\tSet of long posterior ciliary arteries|Long posterior ciliary arteries\tFMA:70778\tUBERON:0001619\tUBERON:0001776|UBERON:0001775|UBERON:0001769\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t25/03/2025 16:52:04\r\nUBERON:8920003\tright marginal artery\tFMA:3818\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000948\tAn artery that is a branch of the right coronary artery. It follows the acute margin of the heart supplying blood to the right ventricle.\twikipedia:Right_marginal_branch_of_right_coronary_artery\tMarginal branch of right coronary artery\tFMA:3818\tUBERON:0001625\tUBERON:0002080\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t25/03/2025 16:52:04\r\nUBERON:8920004\tsegmental renal artery\tFMA:70494\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0002113\tAn artery that branches from the renal artery. The anterior division of the renal artery typically divides into four segmental arteries, whereas the posterior division of the renal artery supplies one segmental artery.\twikipedia:Renal_circulation|doi:10.1148/rg.2021200162|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/arteries-of-kidneys/23888\t\t\tUBERON:0001184\tUBERON:0002113\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t25/03/2025 16:52:04\r\nUBERON:8920005\tsuperior segmental renal artery\tFMA:70499\tUBERON:8920004\tUBERON:0002113\tA segmental renal artery that passes anterior to the renal pelvis, superiorly and laterally. It supplies the superior (apical) lobe of the kidney.\thttps://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/superior-segmental-artery-of-kidney/17005|wikipedia:Renal_circulation\t\t\tUBERON:0001184\tUBERON:0009913\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t25/03/2025 16:52:04\r\nUBERON:8920006\tanterior superior segmental renal artery\tFMA:70500\tUBERON:8920004\tUBERON:0002113\tA segmental renal artery that passes anterior to the renal pelvis, superiorly and laterally towards the superior pole of the kidney. It does not ascend as steeply as the superior segmental artery and does not extend into the superior pole. It supplies the anterosuperior lobe of the kidney, which includes the central anterosuperior region, extending to the lateral aspect and slightly onto the posterior surface of the kidney.\thttps://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/anterior-superior-segmental-artery-of-kidney-left/19263|wikipedia:Renal_circulation\t\t\tUBERON:0001184\tUBERON:0009913\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t25/03/2025 16:52:04\r\nUBERON:8920007\tanterior inferior segmental renal artery\tFMA:70501\tUBERON:8920004\tUBERON:0002113\tA segmental renal artery that passes anterior to the renal pelvis, laterally and angled slightly inferiorly. It supplies the anteroinferior lobe of the kidney, which includes the central anteroinferior region, extending to the lateral aspect and slightly onto the posterior surface of the kidney.\thttps://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/anterior-inferior-segmental-artery-of-kidney/19008|wikipedia:Renal_circulation\t\t\tUBERON:0001184\tUBERON:0009913\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t25/03/2025 16:52:04\r\nUBERON:8920008\tinferior segmental renal artery\tFMA:70502\tUBERON:8920004\tUBERON:0002113\tA segmental renal artery that passes anterior to the renal pelvis, inferiorly and laterally towards the inferior pole of the kidney. It supplies the inferior lobe of the kidney, which encompasses the whole of the inferior pole of the kidney, including the anterior and posterior surfaces.\thttps://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/inferior-segmental-artery-of-kidney/18707|wikipedia:Renal_circulation\t\t\tUBERON:0001184\tUBERON:0009913\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t25/03/2025 16:52:04\r\nUBERON:8920009\tposterior segmental renal artery\tFMA:70503\tUBERON:8920004\tUBERON:0002113\tA segmental renal artery that passes posterior to the renal pelvis and travels laterally, more or less horizontally. It supplies the posterior lobe of the kidney, which includes all of the central-posterior surface of the kidney. This excludes the superior and inferior poles and a small posterolateral portion.\thttps://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/posterior-segmental-artery-of-kidney/22036|wikipedia:Renal_circulation\t\t\tUBERON:0001184\tUBERON:0009913\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t25/03/2025 16:52:04\r\nUBERON:8920020\tdorsal pancreatic artery\tFMA:14787\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000916\tAn artery that branches from the splenic artery and supplies the head, uncinate process, neck, body and tail of the pancreas. It anastamoses with the superior pancreaticoduodenal artery.\twikipedia:Dorsal_pancreatic_artery|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/dorsal-pancreatic-artery/19589|doi:10.1002/ca.22331\tDorsal pancreatic part of splenic artery\tFMA:14787\tUBERON:0001194\tUBERON:0001264\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t2025-05-14T14:34:54Z\r\nUBERON:8920021\tgreater pancreatic artery\tFMA:14792\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000916\tAn artery that branches from the splenic artery and supplies the left half of the body and tail of the pancreas.\twikipedia:Greater_pancreatic_artery|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/great-pancreatic-artery/22884\tGreat pancreatic artery\tFMA:14792\tUBERON:0001194\tUBERON:0001150|UBERON:0001151\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t2025-05-14T14:34:54Z\r\nUBERON:8920022\tcaudal pancreatic artery\tFMA:14793\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000916\tAn artery that branches from the splenic artery and supplies the tail of the pancreas.\thttps://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/artery-to-tail-of-pancreas/24461|wikipedia:Pancreatic_branches_of_splenic_artery|PMID:25665283\tArtery to tail of pancreas\tFMA:14793\tUBERON:0001194\tUBERON:0001151\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t2025-05-14T14:34:54Z\r\nUBERON:8920023\ttransverse pancreatic artery\t\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000916\tAn artery that branches from the dorsal pancreatic artery and supplies the body and tail of the pancreas. It is also known as the inferior pancreatic artery.\tdoi:10.1016/j.pan.2022.02.002|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/inferior-pancreatic-artery/18545\tinferior pancreatic artery\tdoi:10.1016/j.pan.2022.02.002\tUBERON:8920020\tUBERON:0001150|UBERON:0001151\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t2025-05-14T14:34:54Z\r\nUBERON:8920024\tanterior superior pancreaticoduodenal artery\tFMA:14782\tUBERON:0002070\tUBERON:0000916\tAn artery that branches from the gastroduodenal artery and supplies the first and second parts (superior and descending parts) of the duodenum and the head of the pancreas.\tdoi:10.1186/s13244-022-01157-z|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/anterior-superior-pancreaticoduodenal-artery/17510\t\t\tUBERON:0010132\tUBERON:0002114|UBERON:0001069\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t2025-05-14T14:34:54Z\r\nUBERON:8920025\tposterior superior pancreaticoduodenal artery\tFMA:14784\tUBERON:0002070\tUBERON:0000916\tAn artery that branches from the gastroduodenal artery and supplies the first and second parts of the duodenum, distal common bile duct and head of the pancreas.\tdoi:10.1186/s13244-022-01157-z|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/posterior-superior-pancreaticoduodenal-artery/22803\t\t\tUBERON:0010132\tUBERON:0002114|UBERON:0001174|UBERON:0001069\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t2025-05-14T14:34:54Z\r\nUBERON:8920026\tanterior inferior pancreaticoduodenal artery\tFMA:70479\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000916\tAn artery that branches from the inferior pancreaticoduodenal artery. It courses on the anterior surface of the uncinate process continuing on to the head of the pancreas. It supplies the uncinate process, head of the pancreas, and the second and third parts of the duodenum.\tdoi:10.1186/s13244-022-01157-z|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/anterior-inferior-pancreaticoduodenal-artery/24783\t\t\tUBERON:0001195\tUBERON:0010373|UBERON:0001069|UBERON:0002114\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t2025-05-14T14:34:54Z\r\nUBERON:8920027\tposterior inferior pancreaticoduodenal artery\tFMA:70480\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000916\tAn artery that branches from the inferior pancreaticoduodenal artery. It courses posterior to the uncinate process and head of the pancreas. It supplies uncinate process and head of the pancreas, second and third parts of the duodenum.\tdoi:10.1186/s13244-022-01157-z|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/posterior-inferior-pancreaticoduodenal-artery/18074\t\t\tUBERON:0001195\tUBERON:0010373|UBERON:0001069|UBERON:0002114\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t2025-05-14T14:34:54Z\r\nUBERON:8920032\tanterior cecal artery\tFMA:14816\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000916\tAn artery that branches from the ileocolic artery and supplies the anterior portion of the cecum.\twikipedia:Anterior_cecal_artery|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/anterior-cecal-artery/18345\t\t\tUBERON:0001197\tUBERON:0001153\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t2025-06-16T09:40:19Z\r\nUBERON:8920033\tposterior cecal artery\tFMA:14817\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000916\tAn artery that branches from the ileocolic artery and supplies the posterior portion of the cecum.\twikipedia:Posterior_cecal_artery|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/posterior-cecal-artery/22904\t\t\tUBERON:0001197\tUBERON:0001153\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t2025-06-16T09:40:19Z\r\nUBERON:8920034\tcolic branch of ileocolic artery\t\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000916\tAn artery that branches from the ileocolic artery and supplies the cecum and inferior portion of the ascending colon.\thttps://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/colic-branch-of-ileocolic-artery/18777\t\t\tUBERON:0001197\tUBERON:0001153|UBERON:0001156\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t2025-06-16T09:40:19Z\r\nUBERON:8920035\tmarginal artery of Drummond\tFMA:14824\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000916\tAn arterial arcade that connects the superior and inferior mesenteric arteries and supplies the colon.\thttps://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK519560/|wikipedia:Marginal_artery_of_the_colon|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/arteries/marginal-artery/23461\tMarginal colic artery\tFMA:14824\tUBERON:0005616\tUBERON:0001155\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t2025-06-16T09:40:19Z\r\nUBERON:8920036\tascending branch of left colic artery\tFMA:14828\tUBERON:0001637\tUBERON:0000916\tAn artery that branches from the left colic artery and supplies the superior portion of the descending colon, the left colic flexure, and the right one half to one third of the transverse colon.\thttps:/