www.kenhub.com/en/library/anatomy/the-cavernous-sinus\t\t\t\tUBERON:0003712\t\tUBERON:0000007\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600091\tinferior anastomotic vein\tFMA:51239\tUBERON:0001638\tUBERON:0000033\tA vein that is tributary of the transverse sinus and drains blood from the adjacent cortical regions of the temporal lobe. The inferior anastomotic vein forms an anastomosis (connection) between the superficial middle cerebral vein anteriorly and the transverse sinus posteriorly.\twikipedia:Inferior_anastomotic_vein\t\t\t\tUBERON:0001641\t\tUBERON:0001871\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600092\tradial vein\tFMA:22947\tUBERON:0001638\tUBERON:0001460\t\"A vein that is tributary of the brachial vein and drains blood from the lateral structures of the forearm, carpal and metacarpal bones, joints of the hand, and lateral forearm muscles.\"\twikipedia:Radial_veins\t\t\t\tUBERON:0001413\t\tUBERON:0002386|UBERON:0002398\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600093\tulnar vein\tFMA:22950\tUBERON:0001638\tUBERON:0001460\tA vein that is tributary of the brachial vein and drains blood from the hand and medial and posterior aspect of forearm.\twikipedia:Ulnar_veins\t\t\t\tUBERON:0001413\t\tUBERON:0002386|UBERON:0002398\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600103\tanterior internal vertebral venous plexus\tFMA:4869\tUBERON:0001593\tUBERON:0002240\t\"A venous plexus that is tributary of the basivertebral veins and internal vertebral veins, draining blood from the vertebrae and spinal cord. The anterior internal vertebral venous plexus is located within the vertebral canal.\"\twikipedia:Internal_vertebral_venous_plexuses\t\t\t\tUBERON:8600104\t\t\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600104\tintervertebral vein\tFMA:76736\tUBERON:0001638\tUBERON:0002240\t\"A vein that drains blood from the vertebral column and intervertebral discs. In the neck, it is tributary of into the vertebral veins. In the thorax, it is tributary of the posterior intercostal veins. In the lumbar and sacral regions, it is tributary of the lumbar and lateral sacral veins\"\thttps://www.kenhub.com/en/library/anatomy/veins-of-the-vertebral-column\t\t\t\tUBERON:0012199|UBERON:8600105|UBERON:8600056\t\t\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8600105\tlumbar vein\tFMA:70889\tUBERON:0001638\tUBERON:0002355\tA vein that is tributary of the inferior vena cava and drains blood from the posterior abdominal wall and lumbar region.\thttps://www.kenhub.com/en/library/anatomy/lumbar-veins\tset of lumbar veins\tFMA:70889\t\tUBERON:0001072\t\tUBERON:0003697|UBERON:0005462\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489\t2024-06-06T09:53:48Z\r\nUBERON:8420001\tethmoidal vein\tFMA:51770\tUBERON:0001638\tUBERON:0002200\tA vein that accompanies an ethmoidal artery and drains the ethmoidal cells.\twikipedia:Ethmoidal_veins|https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK499826/\t\t\t\t\t\tUBERON:0011241\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-8314-2140\t2024-08-28T09:55:00Z\r\nUBERON:8420002\tanterior ethmoidal vein\tFMA:51771\tUBERON:8420001\t\tAn ethmoidal vein that accompanies an anterior ethmoidal artery. The anterior ethmoidal vein normally drains into the inferior root of the superior ophthalmic vein.\thttps://doi.org/10.1167/iovs.02-0865|https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-40697-3_23\t\t\t\tUBERON:0011192\t\t\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-8314-2140\t2024-08-28T09:55:00Z\r\nUBERON:8420003\tposterior ethmoidal vein\tFMA:51772\tUBERON:8420001\t\tAn ethmoidal vein that accompanies a posterior ethmoidal artery. The posterior ethmoidal vein often drains into a venous network under the orbital roof.\thttps://doi.org/10.1167/iovs.02-0865|https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-40697-3_23\t\t\t\t\t\t\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-8314-2140\t2024-08-28T09:55:00Z\r\nUBERON:8920010\tleft marginal vein\tFMA:4708\tUBERON:0001638\tUBERON:0000948\tA vein that is a tributary of the great cardiac vein (left coronary vein) and drains blood from the left ventricle of the heart. It courses with the left marginal artery as it travels superiorly along the left cardiac border.\twikipedia:Left_marginal_vein|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/cardiovascular-system/veins/left-marginal-vein-of-heart/22447\t\t\t\tUBERON:0006958\t\tUBERON:0002084\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t14/04/2025 13:00:33\r\nUBERON:8920011\tstellate vein of kidney\tFMA:71635\tUBERON:0001638\tUBERON:0002113\tA vein that drains blood from the most superficial zones of the renal cortex. Groups of stellate veins are arranged in a star-like pattern, converging centrally to drain into an interlobular vein.\twikipedia:Stellate_veins|https://www.elsevier.com/resources/anatomy/kidney-lobe/intrarenal-blood-vessels/interlobular-veins-of-kidney/15668\tSet of stellate veins of kidney\tFMA:71635\t\tUBERON:0005168\t\tUBERON:0001225\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t14/04/2025 13:00:33\r\nUBERON:8920012\tsegmental renal vein\t\tUBERON:0001638\tUBERON:0002113\tA vein that is a tributary of the renal vein and drains blood from a segment of the kidney.\thttps://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538298/|doi:10.37532/1308-4038.18.11.26\t\t\t\tUBERON:0001140\t\t\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t14/04/2025 13:00:33\r\nUBERON:8920013\tanterior ciliary vein\tFMA:51798\tUBERON:0001638\tUBERON:0000970\tA vein that is a tributary of the superior ophthalmic vein and drains blood from the ciliary body of the eye.\tdoi:10.1038/s41433-023-02416-z|doi:10.1186/s12886-018-0892-1\t\t\t\tUBERON:0011192\t\tUBERON:0001775\thttps://orcid.org/0000-0001-6757-4744\t14/04/2025 13:00:33\r\nUBERON:8920014\tleft bronchial vein\tFMA:4837\tUBERON:0001592\tUBERON:0002048\tA bronchial vein that drains blood from the bronchi into the accessory hemiazygos vein or the left superior intercostal vein.\thttps://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/books/NBK537353/|wikip